SIMPLE: non
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Non
<hw>Non</hw> <pr>(n⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>No; not. See
<er>No</er>, <pos>a.</pos></def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Non-</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Non-
<hw>Non-</hw> <pr>(n⟦ocr⟧n-)</pr> <pos>pref.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>non</ets>, OL. <ets>noenu</ets>, <ets>noenum</ets>, fr.
<ets>neoenum</ets>, lit., not one. See <er>None</er>.]</ety> <def>A
prefix used in the sense of <sig>not</sig>; <sig>un</sig>-;
<sig>in</sig>-; as in <ex>non</ex>attention, or <ex>non</ex>-attention,
<ex>non</ex>conformity, <ex>non</ex>metallic,
<ex>non</ex>suit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The prefix <xex>non-</xex> may be joined to the leading
word by means of a hyphen, or, in most cases, the hyphen may be
dispensed with. The list of words having the prefix <xex>non-</xex>
could easily be lengthened.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nona</ent>⟦br⟧
